-- Citic Securities to Buy Credit Agricole’s CLSA for $1.25 Billion
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-20T13:28:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/citic-securities-to-buy-credit-agricole-s-clsa-for-1-25-billion.html
Citic Securities Co., China’s
largest brokerage by market value, said it agreed to buy  Credit
Agricole SA (ACA) ’s CLSA unit for $1.25 billion.  Citic, based in Beijing, today completed the previously
agreed purchase of a 19.9 percent stake in CLSA for $310.3
million, according to a statement to the Shanghai stock
exchange. Citic will buy the remaining 80.1 percent stake
fo$941.7 million, subject to it meeting conditions, the company
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
